<body>
  <p>Find your MP by postal code:
    <form action="mps;search" method="get">
      <input type="text" id="postal_code" name="postal_code" size="7" value="" />
      <input type="submit" value="Search">
    </form>
  </p>
 
  <p>This site exists to make data about <a href="http://webinfo.parl.gc.ca/MembersOfParliament/MainMPsCompleteList.aspx?TimePeriod=Current&Language=E">Canadian MPs</a> easier to use, especially for programmers and advocacy organizations. The list is available in plain html, CSV, JSON and XML formats:<br/>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="http://lokobo.com:3000/mps">http://lokobo.com:3000/mps</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://lokobo.com:3000/mps.csv">http://lokobo.com:3000/mps.csv</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://lokobo.com:3000/mps.json">http://lokobo.com:3000/mps.json</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://lokobo.com:3000/mps.xml">http://lokobo.com:3000/mps.xml</a></li>
  </ul>
  Searches by postal code can also be retrieved in all those formats.</p>

  <p>Data obtained through this website is made available at no cost and with no licensing restrictions. Source Code for running the website and obtaining your own copy of the data is also freely available: 
  <a href="http://rubyforge.org/projects/mp-ca-scraper/">http://rubyforge.org/projects/mp-ca-scraper/</a> (<a href="http://rubyforge.org/scm/?group_id=3225">SVN</a>). 
  </p>
  <p>Please forward any questions to chebuctonian using gmail. I've also <a href="http://danieljohn.livejournal.com/tag/canadianmpdata">blogged about this</a></p>


